  "text": "Our work is different from the existing literature as it proposes the implementation of a VoIP monitoring solution, called iMOS, to measure the quality of the VoIP calls at intermediate points in the SDN. The most difficult part of monitoring VoIP calls is obtaining the network delay. The solution in [CITATION_1] uses an intrusive solution to measure the delay, whereas our solution uses information obtained from the actual VoIP call to estimate the network delay.",
